WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:04.265
Previously onSalvation...My fellow Americans,

00:04.308 --> 00:06.963
the unthinkable...

00:07.007 --> 00:08.182
...has become reality.

00:08.225 --> 00:09.574
ALYCIA:
Darius Tanz

00:09.618 --> 00:10.619
is president.

00:10.662 --> 00:13.839
We control one remaining ICBM

00:13.883 --> 00:15.537
carrying 13 warheads.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.930
You're trying to shoot
down RE/SYST's nukes

00:17.974 --> 00:19.236
with the rail gun?

00:19.280 --> 00:20.933
If you make any attempt
to disable those nukes,

00:20.977 --> 00:22.892
RE/SYST will retaliate.

00:22.935 --> 00:24.285
Arrest this man;
he's just confessed

00:24.328 --> 00:26.287
to being an enemy of the
United States of America.

00:26.330 --> 00:29.072
Losing Mr. Cole is a blow
to the solar sail project.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.552
What about Raul Aguirre?

00:30.595 --> 00:32.771
He's the one with
the nanotechnology we need.

00:32.815 --> 00:33.990
I will meet with you,

00:34.034 --> 00:35.948
but there are certain
conditions.

00:35.992 --> 00:37.428
Release Liam Cole,

00:37.472 --> 00:40.475
and I will get RE/SYST
to call off the nukes.

00:40.518 --> 00:43.478
You had no authority
to speak with her!

00:43.521 --> 00:45.915
Jillian, what truth
did you accept today?

00:45.958 --> 00:47.960
This is the only place
I feel safe.

00:51.051 --> 00:53.009
Who the hell do
you work for?
I don't know.

00:53.053 --> 00:54.967
People lie, Fiona,

00:55.011 --> 00:57.753
but that chip
in your neck can't.

00:57.796 --> 01:00.016
Mr. President, we need to...

01:00.060 --> 01:02.105
Sir, we've lost eyes.GRACE: What are you saying?

01:02.149 --> 01:03.193
The president
of the United States

01:03.237 --> 01:04.455
just snuck out
of the White House.

01:18.600 --> 01:20.384
WOMAN:
West Wing.

01:20.428 --> 01:22.386
I'm sorry, the president
is unavailable.

01:22.430 --> 01:23.909
MAN:
West Wing.

01:23.953 --> 01:25.172
I'm sorry.

01:26.564 --> 01:27.696
Can I take a message?

01:27.739 --> 01:28.697
WOMAN:
I'm sorry.

01:28.740 --> 01:30.960
MAN:
He's in a meeting.

01:31.743 --> 01:33.745
All right, listen up.

01:33.789 --> 01:35.921
Nothing I'm about to say
leaves this room.

01:35.965 --> 01:37.314
You are not to discuss this
with anyone.

01:37.358 --> 01:41.318
Not your staff, your spouse,
or your shrink,

01:41.362 --> 01:43.494
under penalty of treason.

01:43.538 --> 01:45.105
The president is missing,

01:45.148 --> 01:47.498
and only the people
in this room are aware.

01:47.542 --> 01:50.327
Director Davis, what does
the FBI know thus far?

01:50.371 --> 01:51.850
The Secret Service had
eyes on the president

01:51.894 --> 01:54.157
at 2100 hours
in the Oval.

01:54.201 --> 01:55.550
They withdrew
to their posts outside.

01:55.593 --> 01:58.161
At 2300, they discovered
that the office was empty.

01:58.205 --> 01:59.815
Now, we believe
that he accessed

01:59.858 --> 02:02.513
the hidden Reagan staircase
to the evacuation tunnels

02:02.557 --> 02:04.167
beneath the Oval Office.

02:04.211 --> 02:07.649
We have been reviewing hours
of security cam footage,

02:07.692 --> 02:09.955
and as of yet... nothing.

02:09.999 --> 02:11.435
Anything from
the D.C. Police?

02:11.479 --> 02:13.176
We've tripled the number
of patrols inside

02:13.220 --> 02:15.874
the Beltway and put out a
description of the president.

02:15.918 --> 02:18.312
Obviously, we can't tell them
exactly who they're looking for

02:18.355 --> 02:20.662
if we wish to maintain
this level of secrecy.

02:20.705 --> 02:23.665
What about foul play?
Could someone have abducted him?

02:23.708 --> 02:25.275
Secret Service
reports that

02:25.319 --> 02:27.277
their agents never
left their posts.

02:27.321 --> 02:28.452
No one got past them.

02:28.496 --> 02:30.541
No one except
the president, you mean?

02:30.585 --> 02:33.109
Okay, we, we don't have time
to place blame, Roland.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.937
Given the recent assassinations
of President Mackenzie

02:34.980 --> 02:37.983
and Monroe Bennett, we need
to explore all possibilities.

02:38.027 --> 02:43.075
Darius... the president is
out there with no protection.

02:43.119 --> 02:45.469
All right,
his life may be in danger.

02:45.513 --> 02:48.124
In the meantime, Mr.
Secretary, we have less

02:48.168 --> 02:50.996
than 24 hours before
that rail gun test,

02:51.040 --> 02:54.174
which will lead to a nuclear
confrontation with RE/SYST.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.306
What are we
doing about it?

02:56.350 --> 02:58.308
STENDAHL:
Nothing.

02:58.352 --> 02:59.918
There's nothing
I can do.

02:59.962 --> 03:02.225
There must be something,
Dr. Stendahl.

03:02.269 --> 03:04.619
President Tanz is the only one
with the legal authority

03:04.662 --> 03:05.924
to stop the rail gun tests.

03:05.968 --> 03:08.013
The project is
under his supervision, and

03:08.057 --> 03:09.580
short of him giving me
a direct order...

03:09.624 --> 03:13.149
What if he's not available
to give you that order?

03:13.193 --> 03:17.022
What exactly is going on,
Ms. Barrows?

03:21.940 --> 03:23.942
What the...?

03:28.295 --> 03:30.253
You lied!

03:30.297 --> 03:32.255
Good morning to you.

03:32.299 --> 03:34.779
You told Darius
RE/SYST would disarm those nukes

03:34.823 --> 03:37.695
if he released me, but they are
still active, every single one.

03:37.739 --> 03:39.219
Got you out, didn't I?

03:39.262 --> 03:41.525
You made a deal,
and you went back on your word.

03:41.569 --> 03:43.092
Darius is never, ever
gonna trust us again.

03:43.135 --> 03:45.050
Trust us?

03:45.094 --> 03:47.139
He's the one who put us in
this untenable position,

03:47.183 --> 03:48.837
threw you in jail.

03:48.880 --> 03:50.839
Liam, he's gone
off the deep end.

03:50.882 --> 03:53.276
You can't deny that his
behavior is reckless.

03:53.320 --> 03:55.147
Reckless is dropping a bomb
on New York City.

03:55.191 --> 03:57.541
He's the one threatening
to use that rail gun

03:57.585 --> 03:58.977
to disarm our nukes.

03:59.021 --> 04:01.284
We're just trying
to save the planet

04:01.328 --> 04:02.807
with the solar
sail project.

04:02.851 --> 04:04.766
Yes, yes, a project
which has hit a dead end

04:04.809 --> 04:06.637
because we wouldn't
collaborate with Darius.

04:06.681 --> 04:08.944
It's happening again.His terms
were unacceptable.

04:08.987 --> 04:10.554
And we don't need
Darius Tanz.

04:10.598 --> 04:11.816
Raul Aguirre is coming.

04:11.860 --> 04:14.863
CROFT:
Mm-hmm, and so is Santa Claus.

04:14.906 --> 04:17.822
What's that supposed
to mean, Croft?

04:17.866 --> 04:19.868
It means the man hasn't
been seen in years.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.826
Rumor is
he never leaves Argentina.

04:21.870 --> 04:23.959
In fact, some people say
he never leaves the house.

04:24.002 --> 04:27.354
And other people say he's dead.

04:27.397 --> 04:29.181
Well, he sent us that message
that he's on the way.

04:29.225 --> 04:31.923
Mm-hmm, and still
there's no sign of him, hmm?

04:31.967 --> 04:33.969
All I'm saying

04:34.012 --> 04:36.841
is, waiting for the Easter Bunny
is not the answer, kids.

04:36.885 --> 04:40.758
The solar sail
is not working as is.

04:40.802 --> 04:43.239
In ten days,
if that thing is

04:43.283 --> 04:45.415
not on its way
to the gravity tractor,

04:45.459 --> 04:47.287
everything we've done

04:47.330 --> 04:49.289
is a waste.

04:51.856 --> 04:53.467
What do you mean?I'm sorry, Mr. Speaker,

04:53.510 --> 04:55.077
but the president
is currently unavailable.

04:55.120 --> 04:58.167
Unavailable? We are on the
brink of nuclear conflict.

04:58.210 --> 05:01.039
Where the hell is he?I'm still awaiting confirmation
of his schedule.

05:01.083 --> 05:03.085
I don't give a rat's ass
about his schedule, young lady.

05:03.128 --> 05:04.434
How-how did you get this job
anyway?

05:04.478 --> 05:05.827
How old are you?

05:05.870 --> 05:08.133
I don't see how that's relevant?

05:08.177 --> 05:10.048
Well, let me tell you
what isrelevant.

05:10.092 --> 05:12.268
Unless President Tanz wants
a vote of impeachment,

05:12.312 --> 05:14.923
he better make himself available
to congressional leadership.

05:14.966 --> 05:17.186
Immediately.

05:33.898 --> 05:35.944
Uh... pesos?

05:35.987 --> 05:38.599
What the hell's this?

05:38.642 --> 05:40.383
Old man?

05:40.427 --> 05:42.820
GUARD:
Whoa, whoa, sir.

05:47.521 --> 05:48.478
Sir, take it easy.

05:50.045 --> 05:51.046
All right, calm down.

05:56.530 --> 05:57.748
ALYCIA:
Hey!

05:57.792 --> 06:00.316
Stand down!
Excuse me. Back off.

06:00.360 --> 06:02.927
Raul Aguirre.
He's here.

06:11.936 --> 06:13.895
What did you tell Stendahl?

06:13.938 --> 06:16.114
Nothing, of course.
Harris, we don't know

06:16.158 --> 06:18.203
whether Darius went on
walkabout or if he's in danger,

06:18.247 --> 06:21.032
and we don't have a lot
of time to figure it out.

06:21.076 --> 06:23.339
I'm aware of that. The entire
governmental apparatus is

06:23.383 --> 06:26.211
working the problem.Yes, but weneed
to work the problem.

06:26.255 --> 06:27.952
And I know where to start.

06:35.351 --> 06:38.006
Harris, leave us alone
for a minute.

06:38.049 --> 06:40.487
It's time to chat
woman to woman.

06:50.105 --> 06:52.673
Get your hands off me.You're an enemy
of the state.

06:52.716 --> 06:53.935
You'll do exactly what we say,

06:53.978 --> 06:55.153
or you'll get the shock
of a lifetime.

06:55.197 --> 06:56.590
Do you understand me?Screw you.

06:56.633 --> 06:58.896
Without a deal on the table,
I'm done talking.

07:08.689 --> 07:10.908
That was just a taste.
This isn't a game show.

07:10.952 --> 07:12.562
There are no deals.

07:12.606 --> 07:14.956
The president
of the United States is missing,

07:14.999 --> 07:18.220
and you're gonna
help us find him. Now.

07:18.263 --> 07:21.266
♪

07:33.235 --> 07:34.541
FIONA:
I already told you.

07:34.584 --> 07:36.847
I have no idea
what happened to Darius.

07:36.891 --> 07:38.632
Perhaps your employer does.

07:38.675 --> 07:41.156
I don't know
who I work for.
Right.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.985
I think it's time
to find out, hmm?

07:46.335 --> 07:47.815
FIONA: Wait. What...? What
are you doing with that?

07:47.858 --> 07:50.208
Putting that chip
back where we found it.

07:50.252 --> 07:51.558
We're gonna
smoke them out.

07:51.601 --> 07:54.386
No. No, n-no, n-no. Please
don't. Please don't. No!

07:57.259 --> 08:00.567
I hope you know
what you're doing, Grace.

08:02.090 --> 08:04.353
Dr. Aguirre, I'm so sorry.
This is

08:04.396 --> 08:08.313
not the welcome that
we intended. I'm Alycia Vrettou.

08:08.357 --> 08:10.968
Sir, I'm Liam Cole.
I just wanted to say,

08:11.012 --> 08:12.840
I've been following your work
on nanomaterials

08:12.883 --> 08:15.364
for the last decade. No me importa.

08:17.409 --> 08:19.063
You speak Spanish, right?

08:19.107 --> 08:20.369
He's looking for a kitchen.

08:20.412 --> 08:22.545
Sir? This way.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.808
Please.

08:27.768 --> 08:30.118
NATE:
Jillian, you can't

08:30.161 --> 08:31.380
take what happened
personally.

08:31.423 --> 08:33.513
Everyone's on a short
fuse right now.

08:33.556 --> 08:34.992
Yeah, but not everyone
gets chewed out

08:35.036 --> 08:37.560
by the speaker of the house
publicly, or has

08:37.604 --> 08:38.996
a chair practically
thrown at them

08:39.040 --> 08:40.563
by the president
of the United States.

08:42.347 --> 08:44.393
Can you forget I said that?
Please?

08:44.436 --> 08:47.309
I just can't
do this anymore.

08:47.352 --> 08:50.312
So, as soon
as the latest crisis is over,

08:50.355 --> 08:53.141
and I can get a word in
with my boss,

08:53.184 --> 08:55.491
I'm going back to Boston.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.275
You're quitting?

08:57.319 --> 09:00.191
I never should have had this job
in the first place.

09:00.235 --> 09:04.195
Hey... don't do something
you're gonna regret.

09:04.239 --> 09:06.415
Come to the meeting
tonight at COPE.

09:06.458 --> 09:08.243
It'll make you
feel better.

09:08.286 --> 09:11.333
: Nate, right now,
I just feel like being alone.

09:13.291 --> 09:15.293
I'm sorry.

09:21.517 --> 09:23.475
What the hell's
he doing?
Shh.

09:43.147 --> 09:44.322
Ah.

09:56.378 --> 09:59.076
So, here's the problem.

09:59.120 --> 10:00.512
We couldn't get enough
of our original fabric

10:00.556 --> 10:01.905
for the solar sail, so

10:01.949 --> 10:04.342
we had to adapt to a thinner
fabric, one that we could

10:04.386 --> 10:06.170
acquire
on our tight schedule.

10:06.214 --> 10:09.130
Unfortunately, every time we
model the unfolding of the sail,

10:09.173 --> 10:12.524
it rips. The new fabric
cannot handle the stress.

10:12.568 --> 10:14.657
But if we use a thicker material
to prevent tearing,

10:14.701 --> 10:17.442
then the added weight makes
the payload too heavy to launch.

10:17.486 --> 10:20.576
But either way, we've got a sail
that can't do its job.

10:20.620 --> 10:22.752
LIAM: Yeah, and I was thinking
maybe there was a way

10:22.796 --> 10:24.319
to redesign the launch package,

10:24.362 --> 10:26.321
maybe use
a hexagonal design instead.

10:32.370 --> 10:35.199
LIAM:
Dr. Aguirre?

10:41.553 --> 10:44.382
Doctor.

10:44.426 --> 10:47.908
I need to think.

10:52.216 --> 10:54.610
Did he just say
"I

10:54.654 --> 10:58.396
Sounded like
"I need to drink."

11:03.227 --> 11:04.838
Dr. Aguirre.

11:06.796 --> 11:08.842
:
Aguirre.

11:08.885 --> 11:14.412
Doctor... why did you come here?

11:14.456 --> 11:16.893
Just to get drunk? Is this
some kind of a game to you?

11:16.937 --> 11:18.503
Because we're-we're
trying to save

11:18.547 --> 11:19.722
the human race
from extinction.

11:19.766 --> 11:22.377
What exactly are you
trying to do?

11:22.420 --> 11:27.208
I have come to repair...

11:27.251 --> 11:30.385
what is torn.

11:30.428 --> 11:33.301
You mean everything?

11:42.789 --> 11:44.704
You're not much
of a talker, huh?

11:44.747 --> 11:46.923
I prefer pictures.

11:53.277 --> 11:55.497
Oh, this is a...
this is a formula for...

11:55.540 --> 11:59.719
Self-repairing nanomaterials.

12:04.636 --> 12:06.334
How long have you been
working on this?

12:06.377 --> 12:08.771
Years. Many,
many, many years.

12:08.815 --> 12:12.514
Science can fix everything,

12:12.557 --> 12:14.734
except for human beings.

12:14.777 --> 12:18.650
We must fix ourselves.

12:30.619 --> 12:33.491
Hey. Look at this.

12:33.535 --> 12:35.842
OP-371 just came back online.

12:35.885 --> 12:37.452
You kidding me. Where?

12:37.495 --> 12:39.846
Four miles from here.

12:39.889 --> 12:41.630
Rock Creek Park.

12:41.673 --> 12:43.632
Her implant goes dark
for three days,

12:43.675 --> 12:44.981
our S&R teams
come up with nothing,

12:45.025 --> 12:46.417
and now she just reappears?

12:46.461 --> 12:47.810
BP's dropping.

12:47.854 --> 12:49.681
Sat levels are way down.

12:49.725 --> 12:51.248
We need an extraction team.

12:51.292 --> 12:53.207
No time. She's crashing.

12:53.250 --> 12:54.469
We got to deal
with this ourselves

12:54.512 --> 12:56.427
before we lose her.

13:04.740 --> 13:07.917
Okay, thanks
for the update.

13:07.961 --> 13:10.485
FBI is using facial
rec software to check

13:10.528 --> 13:12.530
CCTV cams from
all over D.C.

13:12.574 --> 13:14.706
ATMs, red light cameras,
the whole drill.

13:14.750 --> 13:17.492
No sign of him yet.

13:17.535 --> 13:19.886
We'll find him, Grace.

13:19.929 --> 13:22.323
You don't know that.

13:24.542 --> 13:26.718
Grace, I'm worried.

13:26.762 --> 13:27.545
About you.

13:27.589 --> 13:29.983
All this anger...

13:30.026 --> 13:32.812
it's not like you.

13:32.855 --> 13:35.205
You think you have the market
cornered on anger?

13:35.249 --> 13:37.991
My father's in prison
for a crime I committed.

13:38.034 --> 13:39.514
Alonzo's out there.
Who knows what he'll do?

13:39.557 --> 13:41.429
All because
of my bad choices.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.213
For which you blame me.

13:43.257 --> 13:46.390
It's not about blame.

13:46.434 --> 13:48.828
I just don't want
to have any more regrets.

13:48.871 --> 13:51.569
MAN:
Target acquired.

13:56.357 --> 13:57.619
HARRIS:
Maintain your distance.

13:57.662 --> 13:59.708
We don't want
to tip them off.

14:08.717 --> 14:11.372
Crap.

14:18.945 --> 14:20.947
She's gone.

14:35.700 --> 14:38.486
They took the
bait. Move out.

14:45.058 --> 14:47.277
CROFT:
Ooh, self

14:47.321 --> 14:50.237
So this is the snake oil
our friend is selling us.

14:50.280 --> 14:52.456
A solar sail that
magically heals itself

14:52.500 --> 14:53.849
after a little spritz.

14:53.893 --> 14:56.678
It's not magic, Croft,
and it's not snake oil.

14:56.721 --> 14:58.462
Oh.
Okay?

14:58.506 --> 15:01.726
It's a, uh, suspension
that coats the material

15:01.770 --> 15:03.337
in a layer of
interconnecting molecules.

15:03.380 --> 15:06.166
Now, if any connection
is broken,

15:06.209 --> 15:09.952
the molecules rearrange
themselves to repair it.

15:09.996 --> 15:11.214
Manipulating molecules
at that level?

15:11.258 --> 15:12.389
Nobody's cracked that.

15:12.433 --> 15:13.825
How do we know
it's going to work?

15:13.869 --> 15:15.262
Yeah, how about
some proof, Dr. Aguirre?

15:15.305 --> 15:18.004
Other than your scrawlings
on your vanilla latte.

15:18.047 --> 15:21.007
Dr. Aguirre, pardon the
rudeness of my colleague.

15:21.050 --> 15:25.011
No, it's-it's okay.
I-I understand.

15:25.054 --> 15:28.753
My English is not so good,
so, uh, bear with me.

15:28.797 --> 15:30.973
Science is-is just humanity

15:31.017 --> 15:33.019
in-in equations
and-and theorems.

15:33.062 --> 15:37.632
We-we are all broken
in-in some way.

15:37.675 --> 15:40.635
For the weak amongst us,

15:40.678 --> 15:45.031
it-it causes us to collapse,
but for-for the truly strong

15:45.074 --> 15:48.077
we are...
how you say in English?

15:48.121 --> 15:49.992
Tejer.
We-we knit. We knit

15:50.036 --> 15:51.907
ourselves back together

15:51.951 --> 15:56.129
to something greater
than we were before.

15:57.173 --> 16:00.611
Well, that's very poetic,
but it's not proof.

16:00.655 --> 16:03.049
Croft, let him finish.
Stop shooting him down.

16:08.489 --> 16:10.970
GUARD: What the hell
are you doing?

16:13.189 --> 16:14.408
CROFT:
What, are you crazy?!

16:14.451 --> 16:17.106
You could've killed us.Quiet.

16:30.293 --> 16:33.253
Now we go to work.

16:42.914 --> 16:44.481
That was...
Amazing.

16:44.525 --> 16:46.440
Ah!
I have to admit,
you were right

16:46.483 --> 16:47.658
about Aguirre being
the missing piece.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.399
I'm sorry I doubted you.

16:49.443 --> 16:52.446
Oh. Congratulations
to both of us.

16:52.489 --> 16:53.969
All of us, every single one.

16:54.013 --> 16:56.972
We have to tell Nero.

16:57.016 --> 16:58.582
Well, thanks to Aguirre,

16:58.626 --> 16:59.757
the rest of the scientists

16:59.801 --> 17:01.411
are committed
to finishing the solar sail.

17:01.455 --> 17:02.978
You know, we can finally
disarm those nukes

17:03.022 --> 17:05.589
and put an end to this
conflict with Darius.

17:05.633 --> 17:06.851
Liam.

17:06.895 --> 17:08.505
If not now, then when?

17:08.549 --> 17:11.030
Those nukes are the only thing
that's keeping Darius

