20:02.592 --> 20:03.550
What's happening?

20:03.593 --> 20:05.160
The atropine's
not working.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.553
What?

20:06.596 --> 20:07.728
We waited too long.

20:07.771 --> 20:08.946
No. Give her
another injection.

20:08.990 --> 20:10.034
She could stroke out.

20:10.078 --> 20:11.297
She's gonna die.

20:17.955 --> 20:20.349
Come on. Come on! Fiona!

20:24.527 --> 20:26.486
You son of a bitch.

20:28.879 --> 20:31.969
She was dead.
What'd you do to her?TTX.

20:32.013 --> 20:34.363
It's a paralytic agent
found in blowfish poison.

20:34.407 --> 20:36.713
Slows heart rate and
inhibits motor function.

20:36.757 --> 20:39.150
Now we get a question.
Where's Darius Tanz?

20:39.194 --> 20:40.761
The president?

20:40.804 --> 20:42.763
If you know anything
about his whereabouts...

20:42.806 --> 20:45.505
I don't.

20:45.548 --> 20:47.811
I'm not playing.

20:49.378 --> 20:52.163
I don't know
anything. I swear.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.122
Then who do you work for?

20:54.165 --> 20:59.170
You're an accessory to the
assassination of Monroe Bennett.

20:59.214 --> 21:01.129
You don't give us something,
you're gonna be spending

21:01.172 --> 21:02.261
the rest of your life

21:02.304 --> 21:05.351
in a very
unpleasant place.

21:05.394 --> 21:08.876
Company policy regarding clients
is on a "need to know" basis.

21:08.919 --> 21:10.269
What company?

21:11.922 --> 21:13.489
Maybe we'll put the word out

21:13.533 --> 21:15.622
that you're
cooperating with us.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.406
How would your employer
feel about that?

21:17.450 --> 21:19.843
They have eyes everywhere.

21:19.887 --> 21:21.062
HARRIS:
Who?

21:21.105 --> 21:24.065
Q-17.

21:28.765 --> 21:30.027
GRACE:
Harris?

21:30.071 --> 21:32.682
Q-17.

21:32.726 --> 21:34.075
GRACE:
What's Q

21:34.118 --> 21:36.860
They're like a private
CIA. Off the grid.

21:36.904 --> 21:38.645
You want to hire them,
you have to know somebody.

21:38.688 --> 21:40.037
Otherwise, they're ghosts.

21:40.081 --> 21:41.648
Well, someone did hire them.

21:41.691 --> 21:44.477
To sabotage the Ark,
blow up the Supreme Court,

21:44.520 --> 21:46.609
and assassinate
a couple of presidents.

21:46.653 --> 21:48.916
Well, we still haven't tied them
to Mackenzie's death.

21:48.959 --> 21:50.178
But if each of those

21:50.221 --> 21:52.702
is one of their
operatives...

21:52.746 --> 21:54.878
The scope of this thing
is massive.

21:54.922 --> 21:59.187
The question is,
who's pulling their strings?

21:59.230 --> 22:02.843
And is Darius next
on their list?

22:02.886 --> 22:05.759
Harris, we're running
out of time.

22:07.891 --> 22:10.372
JILLIAN:
So...

22:10.416 --> 22:12.374
what are you doing here?

22:12.418 --> 22:14.985
Ah, when one of our members
is in need, we come.

22:15.029 --> 22:17.510
That is incredibly
generous.

22:17.553 --> 22:20.208
Well, you're special.

22:20.251 --> 22:22.993
I've seen that since
the first moment I met you.

22:23.037 --> 22:25.692
Really?

22:25.735 --> 22:27.955
You have wisdom
beyond your years.

22:27.998 --> 22:31.306
Why do you think the president
chose you as his assistant

22:31.350 --> 22:33.264
over all the other people
out there?

22:33.308 --> 22:34.788
I don't know,

22:34.831 --> 22:39.619
but I'm assuming
he regrets it right about now.

22:39.662 --> 22:42.709
So the speaker of the House
dressed you down.

22:42.752 --> 22:44.972
Mm-hmm.The president got angry.

22:45.015 --> 22:46.800
Those aren't reasons to quit.

22:46.843 --> 22:49.846
They're lessons.

22:49.890 --> 22:53.328
The universe has much to teach

22:53.372 --> 22:55.417
if you listen.Oh, I am trying,

22:55.461 --> 22:57.680
but can it speak up a little?

23:04.165 --> 23:07.995
Can you accept
that you have a purpose?

23:09.997 --> 23:12.173
I can.

23:12.216 --> 23:17.570
When a tree is strong, even a
hurricane wind cannot uproot it.

23:17.613 --> 23:20.747
You are strong.

23:20.790 --> 23:22.792
You are wise.

23:22.836 --> 23:25.621
Don't let other people
blow you off your path.

23:41.942 --> 23:43.900
And what's this?

23:43.944 --> 23:46.686
Pisco. You drink.

23:48.949 --> 23:50.690
I don't think so.

23:50.733 --> 23:53.780
Drink, drink, it's
good for the constitution.

23:57.305 --> 23:59.307
Who cares?

24:04.355 --> 24:06.923
You know, 'cause
it's over.

24:06.967 --> 24:08.621
Everything I-I've
believed in,

24:08.664 --> 24:11.232
every choice I have made
has been wrong.

24:11.275 --> 24:16.019
I tried to save the world and
I actually made things worse.

24:17.760 --> 24:21.721
And Darius was right
about... RE/SYST,

24:21.764 --> 24:23.723
about Alycia, all of it.

24:23.766 --> 24:26.334
Every little thing.

24:29.729 --> 24:30.947
What am I doing?

24:30.991 --> 24:32.253
I mean, you probably
can't even understand

24:32.296 --> 24:33.733
half of what I'm saying.

24:35.561 --> 24:37.519
I understand.

24:37.563 --> 24:39.913
More than you know.

24:42.089 --> 24:43.786
:
Just because you're brilliant

24:43.830 --> 24:45.005
doesn't mean
you're always right.

24:48.922 --> 24:50.140
You're still gonna need
that rail gun

24:50.184 --> 24:52.186
to help with the solar sail.

24:52.229 --> 24:55.276
D

24:55.319 --> 24:56.930
: Listen,
we haven't got much time.

24:56.973 --> 24:58.975
ALYCIA:
Gentlemen?

25:01.021 --> 25:02.936
Am I interrupting
anything?

25:02.979 --> 25:06.374
U-Un brindis
por nuevos comienzos.

25:06.417 --> 25:08.507
A toast to new beginnings.

25:08.550 --> 25:10.509
I drink to this.
Yes.

25:27.569 --> 25:29.266
What the hell, Darius?
What's going on?

25:29.310 --> 25:30.790
Where's the real Dr. Aguirre?

25:30.833 --> 25:32.313
Standing right in front of you.

25:32.356 --> 25:33.880
What are you talking about?

25:33.923 --> 25:36.273
Ten years ago,

25:36.317 --> 25:40.408
I created an alter ego,
a nom de plume if you will.

25:40.451 --> 25:44.543
Thus, Dr. Raul Aguirre was born.

25:44.586 --> 25:46.153
But, uh, w

25:46.196 --> 25:47.415
I wanted to
publish certain

25:47.458 --> 25:49.373
controversial research

25:49.417 --> 25:51.201
that was outside
my area of expertise.

25:51.245 --> 25:53.290
Nanomaterials.Yeah.

25:53.334 --> 25:54.553
But the alias stuck,
and-and over time,

25:54.596 --> 25:56.250
the ruse grew more elaborate.

25:56.293 --> 25:58.339
There was a great demand
for the talents of Dr. Aguirre.

25:58.382 --> 25:59.949
So I turned him into a recluse,

25:59.993 --> 26:03.213
uh, an eccentric who
never went anywhere.

26:03.257 --> 26:05.259
Until now.Okay, so-so,

26:05.302 --> 26:06.782
you're pretending
to be Aguirre, but...

26:06.826 --> 26:10.917
but why, is it to sneak in
and sabotage the solar sail?

26:10.960 --> 26:13.702
No, the solar sail is brilliant.

26:13.746 --> 26:15.182
Combined with the
rail gun, it may be

26:15.225 --> 26:17.053
our only hope for survival.

26:17.097 --> 26:19.012
Is this the part where
you tell me that I was right?

26:19.055 --> 26:20.274
Partially right.

26:20.317 --> 26:22.015
You still needed
Dr. Aguirre to solve

26:22.058 --> 26:23.320
your materials problem.All right, it doesn't matter,

26:23.364 --> 26:24.844
it doesn't matter.
I want to know why

26:24.887 --> 26:26.672
you went through all this
to help RE/SYST.

26:26.715 --> 26:29.892
I didn't come here to help.

26:29.936 --> 26:31.851
I needed to get
inside Tanz,

26:31.894 --> 26:35.115
and-and Aguirre
was my entry point.

26:35.158 --> 26:38.640
I'm here to prevent
a nuclear holocaust.

26:38.684 --> 26:41.643
Well, I mean,
you started all of this.

26:41.687 --> 26:44.124
I shouldn't even
be talking to you.

26:44.167 --> 26:46.909
After what you did?
I mean, you threw me in a jail.

26:46.953 --> 26:49.520
You were talking to me like
I was, I was a criminal.

26:49.564 --> 26:52.001
You left me no choice.

26:52.045 --> 26:54.613
Liam.

26:57.354 --> 26:59.661
I did come here to repair
what's been torn.

26:59.705 --> 27:02.577
The two of us have the
power to shut it down

27:02.621 --> 27:06.363
and get back
to what we do: science.

27:06.407 --> 27:08.844
But I need your help.

27:12.152 --> 27:15.459
This chip contains a virus
that'll destroy Tess.

27:15.503 --> 27:17.636
She's the one
controlling those nukes.

27:48.101 --> 27:50.103
DAVIS:
Is this all of it?

27:51.626 --> 27:53.628
Yeah, every last scrap of paper
and digital file

27:53.672 --> 27:55.282
from that warehouse.

27:55.325 --> 27:57.066
Should give us a window
into Q-17's

27:57.110 --> 27:58.285
current operations.

27:58.328 --> 28:00.156
My team will analyze
the documents.

28:00.200 --> 28:01.984
If there's anything of use,
we'll find it.

28:02.028 --> 28:03.769
Yeah.But meantime,

28:03.812 --> 28:06.119
still no sign of the president.

28:06.162 --> 28:08.512
We've come up empty,
Mr. Secretary.

28:08.556 --> 28:11.951
We've got eight hours until
that rail gun fires, Harris.

28:11.994 --> 28:17.434
We need to make some big moves,
and nobody's gonna like them.

28:19.306 --> 28:22.135
You know the plan:
get into the server room.

28:22.178 --> 28:23.745
If this doesn't work...

28:23.789 --> 28:25.138
We're in the same position
we're in right now,

28:25.181 --> 28:26.748
with time running out
and RE/SYST's finger

28:26.792 --> 28:28.271
on the nuclear button.

28:28.315 --> 28:30.099
:
We've got nothing to lose.

28:30.143 --> 28:31.884
Liam?

28:31.927 --> 28:33.537
What's going on?
You said it was important.

28:33.581 --> 28:38.978
Yeah. There's something you need
to know about Dr. Aguirre.

28:40.022 --> 28:41.981
Liam, no!

28:42.024 --> 28:43.112
Are you insane?
What are you...?

28:43.156 --> 28:45.549
LIAM:
There's a traitor in our midst.

28:45.593 --> 28:47.769
Traitor

28:49.249 --> 28:51.033
Darius?

28:53.122 --> 28:55.124
LIAM: I'm sorry,
Darius, but sometimes,

28:55.168 --> 28:57.039
you can't repair what's torn.

29:08.442 --> 29:10.836
HARRIS:
Dr. Stendahl,

29:10.879 --> 29:13.621
that rail gun test cannot
go forward as planned.

29:13.664 --> 29:15.318
I'm under orders from the
president of the United States.

29:15.362 --> 29:17.320
He's the only one
that can stop this test.

29:17.364 --> 29:19.801
We know, Rosetta,
but the president

29:19.845 --> 29:21.847
is missing.

29:23.631 --> 29:25.154
We have to stop this
before it's too late.

29:25.198 --> 29:26.590
In the absence

29:26.634 --> 29:27.983
of the president,
I am giving you

29:28.027 --> 29:30.769
a direct order
to stop this test...

29:30.812 --> 29:34.381
Wait, after all
that's gone on: civil war,

29:34.424 --> 29:37.950
coups, how do I know
that you're not the traitors?

29:37.993 --> 29:39.952
How do I know
that you're not

29:39.995 --> 29:42.781
the ones responsible
for his disappearance?

29:42.824 --> 29:45.696
You're gonna have
to trust us.

29:49.439 --> 29:52.616
I never thought physical
violence was your style.

29:52.660 --> 29:54.662
What were you expecting?

29:54.705 --> 29:56.098
Harsh language?

29:57.752 --> 30:00.799
You have no idea
what's at stake here, do you?

30:00.842 --> 30:03.453
Other than the blood of millions
of innocent civilians

30:03.497 --> 30:05.847
on your hands, I suppose no.

30:05.891 --> 30:07.936
I'm not the one responsible.

30:07.980 --> 30:09.982
You can make this go away.

30:10.025 --> 30:12.680
All you have to do
is hand over the rail gun.

30:12.723 --> 30:14.987
Why don't you just steal it?
You're so very good at that,

30:15.030 --> 30:18.207
aren't you?I didn't steal anything.

30:18.251 --> 30:20.209
I created Tess.

30:20.253 --> 30:22.516
Ugh, again with that.
Wecreated Tess.

30:22.559 --> 30:25.911
And you tried to smuggle out her
source code, but I caught you.

30:28.000 --> 30:29.305
No, you destroyed

30:29.349 --> 30:32.526
my reputation, Darius.

30:32.569 --> 30:34.920
You ruined my career.

30:34.963 --> 30:36.095
No.

30:36.138 --> 30:38.488
You did that.

30:38.532 --> 30:40.055
On your own.

30:48.803 --> 30:50.979
I know where
you came from, Alycia.

30:51.023 --> 30:55.288
A father who treated you
like nothing,

30:55.331 --> 30:56.985
made you feel like nothing.

30:57.029 --> 30:58.857
We had that in common.

30:58.900 --> 31:01.772
It's what made us who we are.

31:01.816 --> 31:06.516
Ruthless perfectionists.

31:06.560 --> 31:09.868
But when you came to me
that day at Tanz,

31:09.911 --> 31:13.306
a disaffected college grad
who snuck away from the tour

31:13.349 --> 31:16.004
to show me her
machine-learning algorithm,

31:16.048 --> 31:20.095
I saw your brilliance, talent.

31:20.139 --> 31:21.923
Your drive.

31:21.967 --> 31:23.969
I nurtured you.

31:24.012 --> 31:27.363
Believed in you.

31:27.407 --> 31:32.934
But... somewhere along the way,

31:32.978 --> 31:36.242
you lost your way.

31:36.285 --> 31:38.635
And you have
the chance right now

31:38.679 --> 31:41.682
to come back from the darkness.

31:41.725 --> 31:44.554
Take it before it's too late.

31:49.733 --> 31:53.433
You have 15 minutes to
change your mind, Darius.

31:53.476 --> 31:55.435
If that rail gun goes off,

31:55.478 --> 31:57.959
Tess will automatically
fire those missiles.

31:58.003 --> 32:00.831
The blood's on your hands,
not mine.

32:00.875 --> 32:03.834
Alycia, you still need me.

32:03.878 --> 32:05.010
Go to hell, Darius.

32:05.053 --> 32:06.272
Wait. Just...

32:11.538 --> 32:12.931
Liam.

32:14.019 --> 32:15.759
What are you doing?

32:15.803 --> 32:17.239
Croft.

32:17.283 --> 32:19.546
Look, it's not
what you think, Croft.

32:19.589 --> 32:21.287
L-Look, we finally have hope.

32:21.330 --> 32:22.810
I am not gonna let you
sabotage it.

32:39.827 --> 32:41.307
Don't be an idiot.

32:41.350 --> 32:43.178
You got Stockholm syndrome.

32:43.222 --> 32:44.963
